## Comparative Summary and Formal Constraints

**Partnerships:** no minimum share capital, at least 2 partners, formation with authenticated private deed (rarely notarized deed), unlimited and joint liability (except limited partners in SAS). **Corporations:** minimum capital (€10,000 for SRL; €50,000 for SPA and SAPA), minimum number of partners 2; notarized deed mandatory for formation; limited liability (except general partners in SAPA, who respond unlimitedly). **Cooperatives:** minimum capital €25 per member; minimum members 9 or 3 for small cooperatives; notarized deed mandatory; limited liability.

**Key Points:**
- **Minimum capital:** €0 for partnerships; €10,000 SRL; €50,000 SPA and SAPA; €25 per member for cooperatives
- **Minimum number of partners:** 2 for partnerships; 2 for corporations (SPA, SRL, SAPA); 9 (3 small) for cooperatives
- **Form:** authenticated private deed for partnerships (rare cases); notarized deed for corporations and cooperatives
- **Liability:** unlimited/joint for partnerships; limited for corporations (except general partners)

**Considerations:**
- Always verify updated legal requirements before formation

